pageContext.claim: “I mean, in the case of China, we charge 2.5 percent when they send a car. And when we send a car into China, they charge us 25 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: China imposed a 15 percent tariff on cars as of July 1, not 25 percent. General Motors sells more cars in China (3.9 million) than in the US (3 million) and saw its China business grow 13 percent in 2016.
